                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/214</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-20T23:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1916, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The terms of Shantung Canal agreement as reported by Gregory to the International
                    Corporation are the most favorable ever obtained by any foreign firm for a loan
                    in China. Prompt ratification by the bankers highly desirable. There is nothing
                    in the present situation that militates against security or advisability of a
                    loan of this sort connected with recognized American undertaking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
